  "prompt": "\"CAS PRES CHQ\" what does this SBI statement message mean?",
  "response": "The message **\"CAS PRES CHQ\"** on an SBI (State Bank of India) statement typically refers to a **\"Cash Presented Cheque\"**. This indicates that a cheque issued from your account has been presented for payment and cleared, resulting in the funds being deducted from your account.\n\nHere\u2019s a breakdown of the term:\n- **CAS**: Cash\n- **PRES**: Presented\n- **CHQ**: Cheque\n\nThis is a standard banking term used to denote that a cheque has been processed and the amount has been debited from your account. If you did not expect this transaction or need further details, you can contact SBI customer care or visit your branch for clarification.",
